msgstr "kdeaccesibility"

#. Tag: keyword
#: index.docbook:44
#, no-c-format
msgid "KMouth"
msgstr "KMouth"

#. Tag: keyword
#: index.docbook:45
#, no-c-format
msgid "text-to-speech conversion"
msgstr "pretvorba besedila v govor"

#. Tag: keyword
#: index.docbook:46
#, no-c-format
msgid "mutual persons"
msgstr "skupne osebe"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:51
#, no-c-format
msgid "Introduction"
msgstr "Uvod"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:53
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&kmouth; is a program that enables persons that cannot speak to let their "
"computers speak. It includes a history of spoken sentences from which the "
"user can select sentences to be re-spoken."
msgstr ""
"&kmouth; je program, ki osebam, ki ne morejo govoriti, omogoča, da pustijo "
"svojim računalnikom govoriti. Vključuje zgodovino izgovorjenih stavkov, iz "
"katere lahko uporabnik izbere stavke, ki jih bo ponovno izgovoril."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:58
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Note that &kmouth; does not include any speech synthesizers. Instead it "
"requires a speech synthesizer installed in the system."
msgstr ""
"Upoštevajte, da &kmouth; ne vključuje sintetizatorjev govora. Namesto tega "
"potrebuje sintetizator govora, nameščen v sistemu."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:65
#, no-c-format
msgid "Using &kmouth;"
msgstr "Uporaba &kmouth;"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:67
#, no-c-format
msgid "The First Time Setup"
msgstr "Prva nastavitev"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:68
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"During the first use of &kmouth;, a wizard is displayed in which you can "
"configure it."
msgstr ""
"Med prvo uporabo &kmouth; se prikaže čarovnik, v katerem ga lahko "
"konfigurirate."

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: index.docbook:74
#, no-c-format
msgid "<screeninfo>Text-to-Speech Configuration</screeninfo>"
msgstr "<screeninfo>Konfiguracija pretvorbe besedila v govor</screeninfo>"

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:80
#, no-c-format
msgid "<phrase>Text-to-Speech Configuration</phrase>"
msgstr "<phrase>Konfiguracija pretvorbe besedila v govor</phrase>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:85
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"With the first page of the wizard you specify the engine and voice that "
"shall be used for the text-to-speech conversion. For more details look into "
"the <link linkend=\"tts-config\">description of the configuration dialog.</"
"link>"
msgstr ""
"Na prvi strani čarovnika določite mehanizem in glas, ki bosta uporabljena za "
"pretvorbo besedila v govor. Za več podrobnosti si oglejte <link linkend="
"\"tts-config\">opis konfiguracijskega pogovornega okna.</link>"

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: index.docbook:93
#, no-c-format
msgid "<screeninfo>Word Completion</screeninfo>"
msgstr "<screeninfo>Dokončanje besed</screeninfo>"

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:99
#, no-c-format
msgid "<phrase>Word Completion</phrase>"
msgstr "<phrase>Dokončanje besed</phrase>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:104
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"With the third page you define the dictionary for a word completion. "
"&kmouth; will parse the &kde; documentation of the chosen language in order "
"to detect the regularity of individual words. Optionally you can compare the "
"word list to an OpenOffice.org dictionary in order to only add correctly "
"spelled words to the word completion."
msgstr ""
"S tretjo stranjo določite slovar za dopolnjevanje besed. &kmouth; bo "
"razčlenil &kde; dokumentacijo izbranega jezika z namenom odkrivanja "
"pravilnosti posameznih besed. Po želji lahko seznam besed primerjate s "
"slovarjem OpenOffice.org, da dodate samo pravilno črkovane besede v dokončno "
"besedo."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:114
#, no-c-format
msgid "The Main Window"
msgstr "Glavno okno"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:115
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The main window of &kmouth; is fairly simple. It consists basically of an "
"edit field into which you type your sentences (the lower white field in the "
"screen shot) and a history of spoken sentences (the upper white field in the "
"screen shot)."
msgstr ""
"Glavno okno &kmouth; je dokaj preprosto. V bistvu je sestavljen iz polja za "
"urejanje, v katerega vnašate svoje stavke (spodnje belo polje na posnetku "
"zaslona) in zgodovine izgovorjenih stavkov (zgornje belo polje na posnetku "
"zaslona)."

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: index.docbook:123
#, no-c-format
msgid "<screeninfo>The main window of &kmouth;</screeninfo>"
msgstr "<screeninfo>Glavno okno &kmouth;</screeninfo>"

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:129
#, no-c-format
msgid "<phrase>The main window of &kmouth;</phrase>"
msgstr "<phrase>Glavno okno &kmouth;</phrase>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:134
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Assuming that you have correctly <link linkend=\"config-dialog\">configured "
"&kmouth;</link> you can use the edit field for entering sentences you want "
"to hear. Once a sentence got spoken it will be appended to the history. From "
"the history you can select sentences to be re-spoken."
msgstr ""
"Ob predpostavki, da ste pravilno <link linkend=\"config-dialog"
"\">konfigurirali &kmouth;</link>, lahko uporabite polje za urejanje za vnos "
"stavkov, ki jih želite slišati. Ko je stavek izgovorjen, bo dodan v "
"zgodovino. Iz zgodovine lahko izberete stavke, ki jih želite ponovno "
"izgovoriti."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:140
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"From the phrase books (located in the line below the tool bar) you can "
"select often used phrases."
msgstr ""
"Iz besednih zvez (nahajajo se v vrstici pod orodno vrstico) lahko izberete "
"pogosto uporabljene fraze."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:146
#, no-c-format
msgid "The Configuration Dialog"
msgstr "Konfiguracijsko pogovorno okno"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:147
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"By using the menu entry <menuchoice> <guimenu>Settings</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Configure &kmouth;...</guimenuitem> </menuchoice> you "
"open the configuration dialog of &kmouth;. This dialog consists of the pages "
"<guilabel>General Options</guilabel> with the two tabs "
"<guilabel>Preferences</guilabel> and <guilabel>Text-to-Speech</guilabel> and "
"the page <guilabel>Word Completion</guilabel>."
msgstr ""
"Z uporabo menijskega vnosa <menuchoice> <guimenu>Nastavitve</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Konfiguriraj &kmouth;...</guimenuitem> </menuchoice> "
"odprete konfiguracijsko pogovorno okno &kmouth;. To pogovorno okno "
"sestavljajo strani <guilabel>Splošne možnosti</guilabel> z dvema zavihkoma "
"<guilabel>Nastavitve</guilabel> in <guilabel>Pretvorba besedila v govor</"
"guilabel> ter stran <guilabel>Dokončanje besed</guilabel>."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:157
#, no-c-format
msgid "The Preferences tab"
msgstr "Zavihek Nastavitve"

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: index.docbook:160
#, no-c-format
msgid "The <guilabel>Preferences</guilabel> tab"
msgstr "Zavihek <guilabel>Nastavitve</guilabel>"

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:166 index.docbook:212 index.docbook:289
#, no-c-format
msgid "Screen shot"
msgstr "Posnetek zaslona"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:171
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <guilabel>Preferences</guilabel> tab contains options that alter the "
"behavior of &kmouth; in certain situations."
msgstr ""
"Zavihek <guilabel>Nastavitve</guilabel> vsebuje možnosti, ki spreminjajo "
"vedenje &kmouth; v določenih situacijah."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:175
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"With the first combo box <guilabel>Selection of phrases in the phrase book</"
"guilabel> you specify which action is triggered by typing the shortcut of a "
"phrase or by selecting a phrase in the <guimenu>Phrase Book</guimenu> menu "
"or in the phrase book bar."
msgstr ""
"S prvim kombiniranim poljem <guilabel>Izbor besednih zvez v besedni zvezi</"
"guilabel> določite, katero dejanje se sproži z vnosom bližnjice besedne "
"zveze ali z izbiro besedne zveze v meniju <guimenu>Zvezek izrazov</guimenu> "
"oz. v besedni vrstici knjige."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:181
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"By selecting <guilabel>Speak Immediately</guilabel> the selected phrase gets "
"immediately spoken and is entered into the history. If you select "
"<guilabel>Insert Into Edit Field</guilabel> the selected phrase is just "
"inserted into the edit field."
msgstr ""
"Če izberete <guilabel>Izgovori takoj</guilabel>, se izbrani stavek takoj "
"izgovori in vnese v zgodovino. Če izberete <guilabel>Vstavi v polje za "
"urejanje</guilabel>, se izbrani stavek samo vstavi v polje za urejanje."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:188
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"With the second combo box, <guilabel>Closing the phrase book edit window</"
"guilabel>, you specify whether the phrase book gets saved if you just close "
"the phrase book edit window."
msgstr ""
"Z drugim kombiniranim poljem, <guilabel>Zapiranje okna za urejanje besedne "
"zveze</guilabel>, določite, ali se besedna zvezka shrani, če samo zaprete "
"okno za urejanje besedne zveze."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:193
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"By selecting <guilabel>Save Phrase Book</guilabel> the phrase book gets "
"saved. If you select <guilabel>Discard changes</guilabel> the changes are "
"discarded and the phrase book is not saved. If you select <guilabel>Ask "
"Whether to Save</guilabel> &kmouth; will ask you whether it shall save the "
"phrase book."
msgstr ""
"Z izbiro <guilabel>Shrani besednjak</guilabel> se besednjak shrani. Če "
"izberete <guilabel>Zavrzi spremembe</guilabel>, se spremembe zavržejo, "
"besednjak pa se ne shrani. Če izberete <guilabel>Vprašanje, ali želite "
"shraniti</guilabel> &kmouth; vas bo vprašal, ali naj shrani besednjak."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:203
#, no-c-format
msgid "The Text-to-Speech tab"
msgstr "Zavihek Pretvorba besedila v govor"

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: index.docbook:206
#, no-c-format
msgid "The <guilabel>Text-to-Speech</guilabel> tab"
msgstr "Zavihek <guilabel>Pretvorba besedila v govor</guilabel>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:217
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"By selecting <guilabel>Use default speech system</guilabel> you tell "
"&kmouth; first to try to use the system speech service prior to calling the "
"speech synthesizer directly. If this succeeds the other configuration "
"entries on this tab are ignored. The system speech service is a &Qt; library "
"which wraps speech-dispatcher on &Linux;, and native speech systems on other "
"platforms. On a Debian based system you need the packages speech-dispatcher, "
"libqt5texttospeech5 and one of the speech-dispatcher modules, usually "
"<application>espeak</application>."
msgstr ""
"Če izberete <guilabel>Uporabi privzeti govorni sistem</guilabel>, poveste "
"&kmouth; najprej poskusite uporabiti sistemsko govorno storitev, preden "
"neposredno pokličete sintetizator govora. Če to uspe, so drugi "
"konfiguracijski vnosi na tem zavihku prezrti. Govorna storitev sistema je "
"&Qt; knjižnica, ki ovija govorni dispečer na &Linux;u in sisteme maternega "
"govora na drugih platformah. V sistemu, ki temelji na Debianu, potrebujete "
"pakete speech-dispatcher, libqt5texttospeech5 in enega od modulov govornega "
"dispatcherja, običajno <application>espeak</application>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:225
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Use the commandline tool <command>spd-conf</command> (Debian package python3-"
"speechd) to adjust settings like rate, pitch, volume, voice type and "
"language &etc; for the default speech system. Additionally <command>spd-"
"conf</command> will let you choose between all installed speech-dispatcher "
"modules, &ie; <application>espeak</application>, <application>festival</"
"application>, <application>flite</application>, <application>mbrola</"
"application> &etc;"
msgstr ""
"Uporabite orodje ukazne vrstice <command>spd-conf</command> (Debianov paket "
"python3-speechd), da prilagodite nastavitve, kot so hitrost, višina, "
"glasnost, vrsta glasu in jezik itd. za privzeti govorni sistem. Poleg tega "
"vam bo <command>spd-conf</command> omogočil izbiro med vsemi nameščenimi "
"moduli dispečerja govora, &ie; <application>espeak</application>, "
"<application>festival</application>, <application>flite</application>, "
"<application>mbrola</application> itd."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:233
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"It is also possible to select the <guilabel>Engine</guilabel> and "
"<guilabel>Voice</guilabel> for the speech system."
msgstr ""
"Za govorni sistem je mogoče izbrati tudi <guilabel>Engine</guilabel> in "
"<guilabel>Glas</guilabel>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:236
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Should the <guilabel>Use default speech system</guilabel> item is not "
"selected you can enter the command for calling the speech synthesize into "
"the edit field of the <guilabel>Alternative</guilabel> panel. With the combo "
"box below the edit field you specify the character encoding that is used for "
"passing the text to the speech synthesizer."
msgstr ""
"Če postavka <guilabel>Uporabi privzeti sistem govora</guilabel> ni izbrana, "
"lahko vnesete ukaz za klic sintetizatorja govora v polje za urejanje plošče "
"<guilabel>Alternativa</guilabel>. S kombiniranim poljem pod poljem za "
"urejanje določite kodiranje znakov, ki se uporablja za posredovanje besedila "
"v sintetizator govora."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:242
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&kmouth; knows two ways of passing the text: If the command expects the text "
"as standard input you select the check box."
msgstr ""
"&kmouth; pozna dva načina posredovanja besedila: Če ukaz pričakuje besedilo "
"kot standardni vnos, označite potrditveno polje."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:246
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The other way is to pass the text as a parameter: Before calling the command "
"&kmouth; replaces certain placeholders with actual content:"
msgstr ""
"Drugi način je posredovanje besedila kot parametra: Pred klicem ukaza "
"&kmouth; nadomesti določene nadomestne oznake z dejansko vsebino:"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:253
#, no-c-format
msgid "Placeholder"
msgstr "Rezervirano mesto"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:253
#, no-c-format
msgid "Replaced with"
msgstr "Zamenjano z"

#. Tag: token
#: index.docbook:256
#, no-c-format
msgid "<token>%t</token>"
msgstr "<token>%t</token>"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:257
#, no-c-format
msgid "The actual text that should be spoken"
msgstr "Dejansko besedilo, ki bi ga bilo treba izgovoriti"

#. Tag: token
#: index.docbook:259
#, no-c-format
msgid "<token>%f</token>"
msgstr "<token>%f</token>"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:260
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The name of a temporary file that contains the text that should be spoken"
msgstr "Ime začasne datoteke, ki vsebuje besedilo, ki naj bo izgovorjeno"

#. Tag: token
#: index.docbook:263
#, no-c-format
msgid "<token>%l</token>"
msgstr "<token>%l</token>"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:264
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The language code associated with the current word completion dictionary"
msgstr "Jezikovna koda, povezana s trenutnim slovarjem za dokončanje besed"

#. Tag: token
#: index.docbook:267
#, no-c-format
msgid "<token>%%</token>"
msgstr "<token>%%</token>"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:267
#, no-c-format
msgid "A percent sign"
msgstr "Znak za odstotek"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:272
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Of course the command for speaking texts is dependent on which speech "
"synthesizer you use. Please look into the documentation of your speech "
"synthesizer for the command for speaking texts."
msgstr ""
"Seveda je ukaz za govorjenje besedil odvisen od tega, kateri sintetizator "
"govora uporabljate. Prosimo, poglejte v dokumentacijo svojega sintetizatorja "
"govora za ukaz za govorjenje besedil."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:280
#, no-c-format
msgid "The Word Completion page"
msgstr "Stran za dokončanje besed"

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: index.docbook:283
#, no-c-format
msgid "The <guilabel>Word Completion</guilabel> page"
msgstr "Stran <guilabel>Dokončanje besed</guilabel>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:294
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <guilabel>Word Completion</guilabel> page contains a list of "
"dictionaries used for the word completion. (&kmouth; will display a combo "
"box next to the edit field in the main window if this list contains more "
"than one dictionary. You can use this combo box in order to select the "
"dictionary that actually gets used for the word completion.)"
msgstr ""
"Stran <guilabel>Dokončanje besed</guilabel> vsebuje seznam slovarjev, ki se "
"uporabljajo za dopolnjevanje besed. (&kmouth; bo poleg polja za urejanje v "
"glavnem oknu prikazal kombinirano polje, če ta seznam vsebuje več kot en "
"slovar. To kombinirano polje lahko uporabite, če želite izbrati slovar, ki "
"se dejansko uporablja za dopolnjevanje besed.)"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:302
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"With the buttons on the right side of the page you can add and delete "
"dictionaries, change the order of the dictionaries or export dictionaries to "
"a file. With the edit field and the combo box below the list you can change "
"the name and the language associated with the dictionary."
msgstr ""
"Z gumbi na desni strani strani lahko dodajate in brišete slovarje, "
"spreminjate vrstni red slovarjev ali izvozite slovarje v datoteko. S poljem "
"za urejanje in kombiniranim poljem pod seznamom lahko spremenite ime in "
"jezik, povezan s slovarjem."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:309
#, no-c-format
msgid "When you add a new dictionary you may choose between several sources:"
msgstr "Ko dodate nov slovar, lahko izbirate med več viri:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:314
#, no-c-format
msgid "Create a new dictionary from the &kde; documentation"
msgstr "Ustvarite nov slovar iz datoteke &kde; dokumentacije"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:315
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you use this source &kmouth; will ask you for the intended language and "
"afterwards parse the &kde; documentation. The frequentness of the individual "
"words is detect by simply counting the occurrences of each word. Optionally "
"you can compare the word list to an OpenOffice.org dictionary in order to "
"only add correctly spelled words to the new dictionary."
msgstr ""
"Če uporabljate ta vir &kmouth; vas bo vprašal za želeni jezik in nato "
"razčlenil &kde; dokumentacijo. Pogostost posameznih besed se zazna s "
"preprostim štetjem pojavitev vsake besede. Po želji lahko primerjate seznam "
"besed s slovarjem OpenOffice.org, da dodate samo pravilno črkovane besede v "
"novi slovar."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:325
#, no-c-format
msgid "Create a new dictionary from a file"
msgstr "Ustvarite nov slovar iz datoteke"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:326
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you use this source &kmouth; will ask you for the intended file. You may "
"either select an &XML; file, a standard text file or a file containing a "
"word completion dictionary created by either &kmouth; or GOK (the GNOME On-"
"screen Keyboard). If you select a standard text file or an &XML; file the "
"frequentness of the individual words is detected by simply counting the "
"occurrences of each word. Optionally you can compare the word list to an "
"OpenOffice.org dictionary in order to only add correctly spelled words to "
"the new dictionary."
msgstr ""
"Če uporabljate ta vir &kmouth; vas bo vprašal za želeno datoteko. Izberete "
"lahko &XML; datoteko, standardno besedilno datoteko ali datoteko, ki vsebuje "
"slovar za dopolnjevanje besed, ki ga ustvari &kmouth; ali GOK (zaslonska "
"tipkovnica GNOME). Če izberete standardno besedilno datoteko ali &XML; "
"pogostost posameznih besed se zazna s preprostim štetjem pojavitev vsake "
"besede. Po želji lahko primerjate seznam besed s slovarjem OpenOffice.org, "
"da dodate samo pravilno črkovane besede v novi slovar."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:339
#, no-c-format
msgid "Create a new dictionary from a folder"
msgstr "Ustvarite nov slovar iz mape"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:340
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you use this source &kmouth; will ask you for the intended folder. "
"&kmouth; will open all files in that folder and its subfolders. Each file is "
"either loaded as a completion dictionary, as an &XML; file or as a standard "
"text file. In the latter two cases the occurrences of each individual word "
"in the file is counted. Optionally you can compare the word list to an "
"OpenOffice.org dictionary in order to only add correctly spelled words to "
"the new dictionary."
msgstr ""
"Če uporabljate ta vir &kmouth; vas bo vprašal za želeno mapo. &kmouth; bo "
"odprl vse datoteke v tej mapi in njenih podmapah. Vsaka datoteka se naloži "
"bodisi kot dopolnitveni slovar, kot &XML; datoteko ali kot standardno "
"besedilno datoteko. V zadnjih dveh primerih se štejejo pojavitve vsake "
"posamezne besede v datoteki. Po želji lahko primerjate seznam besed s "
"slovarjem OpenOffice.org, da dodate samo pravilno črkovane besede v novi "
"slovar."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:351
#, no-c-format
msgid "Merge dictionaries"
msgstr "Združi slovarje"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:352
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can use this option in order to merge the available dictionaries. "
"&kmouth; will ask you which dictionaries should be merged and how the "
"individual dictionaries should be weighted."
msgstr ""
"To možnost lahko uporabite za združevanje razpoložljivih slovarjev. &kmouth; "
"vas bo vprašal, katere slovarje je treba združiti in kako naj bodo posamezni "
"slovarji ponderirani."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:359
#, no-c-format
msgid "Create an empty word list"
msgstr "Ustvarite prazen seznam besed"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:360
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can use this option in order to create a blank dictionary without any "
"entries. As &kmouth; automatically adds newly typed words to the "
"dictionaries it will learn your vocabulary with the time."
msgstr ""
"To možnost lahko uporabite za ustvarjanje praznega slovarja brez vnosov. Kot "
"&kmouth; samodejno doda na novo vnesene besede v slovarje in se sčasoma "
"nauči vašega besedišča."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:370
#, no-c-format
msgid "The Phrase Book Edit Window"
msgstr "Okno za urejanje besednjaka"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:371
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"By using the menu entry <menuchoice> <guimenu>Phrase Books</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Edit...</guimenuitem> </menuchoice> you open the phrase "
"book edit window."
msgstr ""
"Z uporabo menijskega vnosa <menuchoice> <guimenu>Besednjaki</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Uredi...</guimenuitem> </menuchoice> odprete okno za "
"urejanje besednjakov."

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: index.docbook:380
#, no-c-format
msgid "The phrase book edit window"
msgstr "Okno za urejanje besednjaka"

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:386
#, no-c-format
msgid "Screenshot"
msgstr "Posnetek zaslona"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:391
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The main area of the phrase book edit window is divided into two parts. "
"Within the upper part the phrase books are displayed in some tree structure."
msgstr ""
"Glavno območje okna za urejanje besednjaka je razdeljeno na dva dela. "
"Znotraj zgornjega dela so besednjaki prikazani v drevesni strukturi."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:396
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Within the lower part you may modify a selected item. If you have selected a "
"phrase you can modify the contents of the phrase as well as its shortcut. If "
"you have selected a phrase book you can only change its name."
msgstr ""
"V spodnjem delu lahko spremenite izbrano postavko. Če ste izbrali frazo, "
"lahko spremenite vsebino fraze in njeno bližnjico. Če ste izbrali besednjak, "
"lahko spremenite samo njegovo ime."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:402
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Actions like adding new phrases and phrase books and deleting selected "
"phrases and phrase books can be done by selecting them in either the menu "
"bar, the toolbar or a pop up menu."
msgstr ""
"Dejanja, kot je dodajanje novih besednih zvez in besednih zvezkov ter "
"brisanje izbranih besednih zvez in besednjakov, lahko izvedete tako, da jih "
"izberete v menijski vrstici, orodni vrstici ali v pojavnem meniju."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:407
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can change the order of the phrase books and phrases by dragging them to "
"their new places or by using the arrow keys while the &Alt; key is pressed."
msgstr ""
"Vrstni red besednjakov in besednih zvez lahko spremenite tako, da jih "
"povlečete na nova mesta ali uporabite puščične tipke, medtem ko je "
"pritisnjena. tipka &Alt;."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:417
#, no-c-format
msgid "Command Reference"
msgstr "Referenca ukazov"

